# Business Rules

Always follow these rules.

## General

- The app must be simple, accurate, and easy to audit.
- Do not add complex workflows unless explicitly requested.
- Do not add many statuses/enums.
- Do not add microservices.
- Do not add API Gateway.
- Do not add RabbitMQ/Kafka.
- Do not add event-driven architecture.
- Do not add complex role permissions.

## Tuition package

- One classroom can have many tuition packages.
- A student chooses one package when enrolling.
- Package name, total sessions, and price must be snapshotted when creating student package/invoice.
- Later changes to original tuition package must not affect old invoices or enrollments.
- TuitionPackage is a template only.

## Enrollment

- Student cannot have two ACTIVE enrollments in the same classroom.
- Enrollment must validate that the selected package belongs to the classroom.
- Enrollment creates StudentPackage and first Invoice automatically.
- Enrollment does not create Payment automatically.

## Invoice and payment

- Payment is the source of truth for paid amount.
- Do not allow manual editing of paidAmount.
- paidAmount = sum(valid payments).
- remainingAmount = finalAmount - paidAmount.
- Canceled payments must not be counted.
- Do not hard delete payments.
- If a payment is wrong, cancel it with reason.
- In V1, do not allow overpayment.
- Do not allow payment for canceled invoice.
- Do not allow payment for fully paid invoice.
- Money operations must use BigDecimal.
- Money operations must be transactional.
- Money operations must have tests.

## Debt

- Debt is calculated from unpaid or partially paid invoices.
- Canceled invoices are not counted as debt.
- Fully paid invoices are not counted as debt.
- Debt must not be manually entered.

## Revenue

- Revenue is calculated from valid payments only.
- Canceled payments are not counted.
- Invoice amount is not revenue until paid.

## Attendance

- PRESENT counts as one used session.
- ABSENT counts as one used session.
- EXCUSED does not count as used session and creates makeup credit.
- CANCELED class session does not count for any student.
- Do not mark attendance for canceled sessions.
- One student has one attendance record per session.

## Makeup

- Approved/excused absence creates makeup credit.
- Unexcused absence does not create makeup credit.
- Canceled class session should allow creating makeup session for the class.
- Do not automatically refund money for absence in V1.

## Package change

- Do not edit old package directly.
- Do not edit old invoice directly.
- Close old student package.
- Calculate used sessions.
- Calculate used amount = usedSessions * oldPackageUnitPrice.
- Calculate paid amount from valid payments.
- Calculate credit/debt.
- If student has credit, subtract it from new invoice.
- If student has debt, add it to new invoice.
- Create new student package.
- Create new invoice with adjustment.
- Save package change log.
- Save activity log.
- Package change must be transactional and tested.
